{{Infobox Officeholder |name =Abdulla Shahid |image = |order = |office =[[People’s_Majlis#The_Speaker|Speaker of the 17th People’s Majlis]] |president =[[Mohamed Nasheed]], [[Mohamed Waheed Hassan Manik]] |term_start =29 May 2009 |term_end = |predecessor =[[Mohamed Shihab]] |successor = |office2 =[[People’s Majlis|Member of Parliament]] - Keyodhoo Constituency |deputy2 = |term_start2 =9 May 2009 |term_end2 = |predecessor2 = |successor2 = |office3 =Minister of Foreign Affairs |deputy3 = |term_start3 =23 August 2007 |term_end3 =11 November 2008 |predecessor3 = |successor3 = |office4 =President’s Member to the Special Majlis |term_start4 = |term_end4 = |predecessor4 = |successor4 = |office5 =President’s Member to the [[People’s Majlis]] |term_start5 = |term_end5 = |preceded5 = |succeeded5 = |office6 = Vaavu Atoll Member to the Special Majlis |term_start6 = |term_end6 = |preceded6 = |succeeded6 = |office7 = Executive Secretary to the [[Maumoon Abdul Gayoom|President]] |term_start7 = |term_end7 = |preceded7 = |succeeded7 = |birth_name = |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |nationality =[[Maldivians|Maldivian]] |party =[[Dhivehi Rayyithunge Party|DRP]] |spouse = |children = 2 sons & a daughter |residence = |alma_mater =Canberra College of Advanced Education, Australia [[Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy]], USA |religion =[[Islam]] |signature = |website = }} '''Abdulla Shahid''' ([[Dhivehi language|Dhivehi]]: ޢަބްދުﷲ ޝާހިދު) is the current and 17th [[People’s_Majlis#The_Speaker|Speaker of the People’s Majlis]], of the [[Maldives]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.majlis.gov.mv/en/speaker-of-the-majlis/ | title=The Honorable Abdulla Shahid, MP, the Speaker of People’s Majlis | accessdate=September 28, 2012}}</ref> He was elected to the position of the [[People’s_Majlis#The_Speaker|Speaker of the People’s Majlis]] on 28th May 2009 after winning 42 votes out of 75 votes and has been [[People’s_Majlis#The_Speaker|Speaker of the People’s Majlis]] since 29th May 2009 <ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.haveeru.com.mv/english/details/26459 | title=Opposition members elected to position of Majlis Speaker, Deputy Speaker | work=newspaper | date=May 30, 2009 | agency=Haveeru Daily | accessdate=September 28, 2012 | location=Maldives}}</ref> Abdulla Shahid is a member of [[Dhivehi Rayyithunge Party|DRP]] and is the parliament member for [[Keyodhoo (Vaavu Atoll)|Keyodhoo constituency]] after getting 43.26% of the votes held on [[Maldivian parliamentary election, 2009|2009]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.maldivesmajlis.com/v2_dhaairaa.php?did=37 | title=J02 - Keyodhoo Constituency | accessdate=September 28, 2012}}</ref>
Shahid previously served as Minister of Foreign Affairs from 23 August 2007 to 11 November 2008<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.majlis.gov.mv/en/speaker-of-the-majlis/ | title=The Honorable Abdulla Shahid, MP, the Speaker of People’s Majlis | accessdate=September 28, 2012}}</ref> in the presidency of then [[Maumoon Abdul Gayoom|President Maumoon Abdul Gayyoom]]. Earlier he was appointed as Minister of State for Foreign Affairs in 2005.
Abdulla Shahid has been serving the Maldivian legislature since 1993 and has been a Member of Parliament continuously since 1995.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://foreign.gov.mv/new/tpl/show/content/ashahid | title=His Excellency Mr. Abdulla Shahid,MP ''A Biographical Note'' | publisher=Foreign Ministry of Maldives | accessdate=September 28, 2012}}</ref>
